article.headline: Robert Morris 72, Fordham 66
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jeremy Chappell scored a game-high 25 points to lead Robert Morris to a 72-66 win over Fordham on Sunday. Jimmy Langhurst had 12 points, seven steals and six assists for the Colonials (5-2). Bryant Dunston paced the Rams (3-4) with 15 points, seven rebounds and five blocked shots. Brenton Butler scored 14 points while Sebastien Greene had 12 and a game-high 11 rebounds. There were 15 lead changes before Butler's 3-pointer gave Fordham a 60-59 edge at 7:13. A.J. Jackson's jumper and Bateko Francisco's 3-pointer highlighted a 7-1 surge that put the Colonials in command, 66-61, with 4:14 to go. Fordham pulled to 68-66 on Dunston's layup with 1:23 to play. The score was tied at 37 at halftime.
